SUMMARY:Autonomous AI Agents — Zero to Build in 3 Hours
DESCRIPTION:AI & data event Mar 12 Bellevue with AWS & Salesforce leaders\, workshops\, and networking for tech pros from 25+ companies.\nJoin us for an exclusive evening of session\, workshop\, insights\, innovation\, and high-impact networking with senior technology leaders shaping the future of Data\, AI\, and Security. \n📅 Date: 12th March\n📍 Location: Bellevue City Hall \nAgenda:\n4:30 PM – 5:30 PM: Check-in & Networking\n5:30 PM – 6:00 PM: Jason Levine\nHead of UX\, Agentic AI Experiences at Amazon Web Services\nTopic to be announced\n6:00 PM – 7:00 PM: Thercio Brandao\nPrincipal AI FDE Engineer at Salesforce\nBuilding Autonomous AI Agents\n7:00 PM – 8:00 PM: Networking & Community Connections \nWhy Attend? \nLearn from leaders driving AI innovation at Amazon Web Services and Salesforce\nGain practical enterprise AI insights and a hands-on workshop.\nNetwork with professionals from 25+ leading companies\nEnjoy pizza\, meaningful conversations\, and community connections\nDetailed session topics will be shared soon. \nWho Should Attend: \nData professionals\, AI practitioners\, security experts\, technology leaders\, founders\, architects\, and innovators passionate about AI.\nThis edition of Seattle Data AI & Security features confirmed speakers from global technology leaders\, bringing expertise in Agentic AI\, Generative AI\, product design\, and enterprise AI transformation.\nFollow Seattle Data AI & Security on LinkedIn\, YouTube\, and our website for updates.
