SUMMARY:Pi Day Community Math Festival
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a joyful celebration of math\, community\, and curiosity as the Seattle Universal Math Museum (SUMM) opens the doors to its first-ever public-facing space! The SUMM Community Math Festival marks our grand opening at Kent Station and kicks off what will become an annual Pi Day tradition. \nThis free\, family-friendly festival invites learners of all ages to explore hands-on math activities\, playful puzzles\, and interactive experiences designed to spark wonder and confidence. Whether you’re a longtime math lover or just passing by\, you’re welcome to jump in\, try something new\, and discover that math really is for everyone. \nWhat to expect: \nEngaging\, hands-on math activities for kids\, teens\, and adults \nWalk-up friendly experiences perfect for mall visitors and families \nA warm introduction to SUMM as a welcoming\, creative math destination \nPi(e) for a Purpose — a bake sale featuring delicious treats \nA fun raffle with fabulous prizes\, supporting SUMM’s community programs \nCome celebrate Pi Day\, enjoy something sweet\, try your hand at playful math\, and help us launch a new community space built on curiosity\, creativity\, and connection. We can’t wait to celebrate with you!
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/pi-day-community-math-festival/
LOCATION:Seattle Universal Math Museum\, 437 Ramsay Way\, Kent\, WA\, 98032\, United States
CATEGORIES:Arts,Educational events,Family events,Games,Science
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://cdn.geekwire.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/3.14-Event-Facebook-Cover.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Seattle Universal Math Museum":MAILTO:info@seattlemathmuseum.org
END:VEVENT
