SUMMARY:Facilitation Lab Seattle with Amanda Baker and Voltage Control
DESCRIPTION:Led by Amanda Baker\, this session follows the Practice Playground format: an interactive\, rotating structure where participants step into the facilitator role\, role-play real scenarios\, and offer constructive feedback. It’s practical\, energizing\, and grounded in real-world challenges — not theory. \nBring a current facilitation dilemma: a workshop you’re shaping\, a team dynamic that needs attention\, or a moment you’d like to navigate differently next time. You’ll test ideas\, gain new perspectives\, and make concrete progress in a supportive environment. \nWhether you facilitate or actively participate\, you’ll leave with sharper tools\, stronger confidence\, and insights you can immediately apply to your work. \nJoin a community of people committed to creating better conversations and more effective group experiences.
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/facilitation-lab-seattle-withg-amanda-baker-and-voltage-control/
