SUMMARY:AI Madness: 16 Tools. One Champion. North Sound Decides.
DESCRIPTION:Which AI tools are actually worth your time — and which ones are all hype? \n​We’re settling it the only way that makes sense in March: a bracket-style showdown. 16 AI tools go head-to-head across four categories. You debate. You vote. One champion gets crowned. \n​Whether you’re a founder who lives in ChatGPT\, a small business owner who just started using Canva’s AI features\, or someone who keeps hearing about AI but hasn’t found the right entry point — this is your night. \n​📍Hemlock State Brewing Co.\n​📅Thurs\, Mar 19\n​⏰5:00–7:30 PM \n​THE BRACKET\n​🧠THE BRAINS(AI Assistants) ChatGPT vs Perplexity | Claude vs Gemini\n​🎨THE CREATIVES(Content & Design) Canva Magic Studio vs Adobe Firefly | Midjourney vs DALL·E 3\n​⚙️THE OPERATORS(Productivity & Business) Microsoft Copilot vs Grammarly | Notion AI vs Zapier AI\n​🔬THE SPECIALISTS(Niche & Emerging) GitHub Copilot vs Otter.ai | Runway vs Descript \n​AGENDA\n​*5:00 PM – Open Networking + Fill Out Your Bracket Prediction Sheet\n​*5:30 PM – Welcome & Rules\n​*5:40 PM – Round of 16: Lightning Pitches + Crowd Votes\n​*6:05 PM – Elite 8: Table Debates (Small Group Rounds)\n​*6:25 PM – Final 4: Full Room Showdown\n​*6:40 PM – Championship + Open Discussion\n​*7:00 PM – Networking Wind-Down \n​WHO THIS IS FOR\n*​Small business owners and entrepreneurs\n​*Tech professionals\, contractors\, and startup founders\n​*Anyone curious about AI tools — no technical or hooper background needed \n​WHAT YOU’LL WALK AWAY WITH\n*​A clear picture of which AI tools are worth trying for YOUR work\n​*Real-world tips from people actually using these tools daily\n​*A network of fellow innovators across the North Sound\n​*Bragging rights if your bracket predictions hold up \n​No slides. No lectures. Just a bracket\, good drinks\, and real conversation about what’s working with AI. \n​Drinks and connections await — RSVP now (attendance is FREE)! \n​Adam & Ryan
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/ai-madness-16-tools-one-champion-north-sound-decides/
LOCATION:Hemlock State Brewing Co.\, 23601 56th Ave W Suite 400\, Mountlake Terrace\, 98043\, United States
